└── frontend/
├── src/
│   ├── App.js
│   ├── App.css
│   ├── Login.js
│   └── Items.js
├── public/
├── package.json
└── .env

---

## How to Run the Project

### Backend (Go)

1. Open terminal
2. Navigate to backend folder
   cd backend
3. Install dependencies
   go mod tidy
4. Run server
   go run .
5. Backend runs at:
   [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)

A db.json file will be created automatically.

---

## Frontend (React)

1. Open a new terminal
2. Navigate to frontend folder
   cd frontend
3. Install dependencies
   npm install
4. Start development server
   npm start

Frontend runs at:
[http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) or [http://localhost:3001](http://localhost:3001)

Note: ESLint is disabled for local development through .env
DISABLE_ESLINT_PLUGIN=true

---

## User Flow (As Required in Assessment)

1. User opens login page
2. Enters username and password
3. On success → redirected to Items page
4. Items list displayed with Add to Cart buttons
5. Top menu shows:
   • Checkout
   • Cart
   • Order History
   • Logo + Cart badge
6. Cart button → shows cart items (cart_id, item_id) in alert
7. Order History button → shows order IDs in alert
8. Checkout converts the cart to an order
9. Success alert displayed

---

## API Endpoints

### Users

POST /users
Creates a new user
Body: { "username": "rupesh", "password": "1234" }

POST /users/login
Returns token
Body: { "username": "rupesh", "password": "1234" }

GET /users
Lists all users

---

### Items

POST /items
Creates new item

GET /items
Lists all items
Used on Items screen

---

### Carts (Token Required)

POST /carts/
Creates cart or adds item to cart
Header: Authorization: Bearer <token>

GET /carts
Lists all carts
Used in Cart alert

---

### Orders (Token Required)

POST /orders/
Converts cart into order
Body: { "cart_id": 1 }

GET /orders
Lists all orders
Used in Order History alert

---

## Authentication

• User logs in and receives a token
• Token is required for cart and order operations
• Only one active token per user

---

## Frontend Screens

Login Screen
• Username
• Password
• Login button
• Invalid credentials → alert

Items Screen
• Items listed as cards
• Add to Cart buttons
• Checkout, Cart, Order History buttons
• Premium UI with gradients, shadows, responsive cards
• Cart badge shows number of items

Alerts
• Cart JSON data
• Order IDs
• Order successful

---

## Data Storage

• All data stored in db.json
• Updated automatically on every change
• No SQL databases required

